RDS: Launch three instances with users and cpu workload information.
RDS: Backup to S3.
IAM: Create a group, add three users there.
EC2: Launch 3 instances. Add each user to the specific instance.
EC2: Install cpu stress software. Should be able to start / stop instance.
EC2: Report high usage system. Monitor instance.

Design:
RDS Class - With all RDS related actions.
     launchInstance (storage, cpu workload, users), backupInstance(createDBSnapshop)
EC2 Class - With all EC2 related actions.
     launchInstance(name, users, storage etc), addUsersToInstance()
IAM class - with all IAM related actions
     createUser()
Main Class - Linking all three classes